search_query: New Mexico History Museum/Palace of Governors Santa Fe museum
extract: The Palace of the Governors (Spanish: Palacio de los Gobernadores) is an adobe structure built in the Territorial Style of Pueblo architecture on Palace Avenue in Santa Fe, New Mexico. Located within the Santa Fe Historic District along the Santa Fe Plaza between Lincoln and Washington avenues, it served as the seat of government for New Mexico for centuries, having been established as the capitol building of Nuevo MÃ©xico in 1610. It was New Mexico's seat of government until 1901.
